4. Implementation and Deployment

4.1 Development Methodology

Agile-Safety Hybrid Approach:

```
Sprint Planning → Development → Safety Review → 
Verification Testing → Documentation → 
Integration Testing → System Testing → Release
```

Version Control:

· Code Repository: Git with signed commits
· Branch Strategy: GitFlow with protected branches
· Code Review: Mandatory review by safety engineers
· Static Analysis: Automated code quality and security checks

Continuous Integration/Deployment:

```
Code Commit → Build → Unit Tests → Static Analysis → 
Safety Analysis → Integration Tests → Performance Tests → 
Deployment to Test Environment → Acceptance Tests → 
Deployment to Production (with canary rollout)
```

4.2 Deployment Strategies

Blue-Green Deployment:

```
1. Deploy new version to green environment
2. Run health checks on green environment
3. Switch traffic from blue to green
4. Monitor green environment for issues
5. Rollback to blue if issues detected
```

Canary Deployment:

```
Stage 1: 1% of traffic for 5 minutes
Stage 2: 5% of traffic for 10 minutes
Stage 3: 25% of traffic for 15 minutes
Stage 4: 50% of traffic for 20 minutes
Stage 5: 100% of traffic for 30 minutes
Success Criteria: Error rate < 0.1%, Latency < 100ms
```

Rolling Update:

```
Batch Size: 1 node at a time
Wait Time Between Batches: 60 seconds
Health Check Interval: 10 seconds
Max Failed Batches: 1 before rollback
```

4.3 Migration Path

Legacy System Integration:

```
Phase 1: Parallel operation with data synchronization
Phase 2: Gradual transition of non-safety functions
Phase 3: Safety system cutover with manual backup
Phase 4: Full transition and legacy system decommissioning
```

Timeline:

· Phase 1 (Months 1-6): Foundation and basic functionality
· Phase 2 (Months 7-18): Advanced features and integration
· Phase 3 (Months 19-24): Testing and certification
· Phase 4 (Months 25-30): Pilot deployment
· Phase 5 (Months 31-36): Full deployment

