5. Case Studies and Applications

5.1 Large Nuclear Power Plant (1300 MWe PWR)

Challenge: Modernize 40-year-old analog control systems while maintaining continuous operation.

Solution:

· Implemented NEOS in parallel with existing systems
· Used digital twin for operator training and procedure validation
· Gradual cutover of control systems during planned outages

Results:

· Capacity Factor: Increased from 85% to 92%
· Forced Outage Rate: Reduced by 45%
· Maintenance Costs: Reduced by 28%
· Safety System Response Time: Improved from 500ms to 50ms

5.2 Small Modular Reactor (SMR) Deployment

Challenge: Optimize fleet operations for distributed energy generation.

Solution:

· NEOS deployed across 12 SMR units
· Centralized monitoring with distributed control
· AI-driven load following and predictive maintenance

Results:

· Construction Time: Reduced by 40%
· Overnight Capital Cost: Reduced by 30%
· Operational Flexibility: Enabled rapid load following (0-100% in 30 minutes)
· Grid Stability: Enhanced through distributed generation

5.3 Medical Isotope Production Facility

Challenge: Optimize production of Tc-99m and other medical isotopes with short half-lives.

Solution:

· NEOS integrated with research reactor
· Real-time optimization of irradiation parameters
· Supply chain integration with hospitals

Results:

· Production Yield: Increased by 22%
· Waste Reduction: Decreased by 35%
· Supply Reliability: Improved to 99.9%
· Cost per Dose: Reduced by 40%

5.4 Space Nuclear Power System

Challenge: Design and operate nuclear power system for Mars mission.

Solution:

· NEOS adapted for space environment
· Radiation-hardened components
· Autonomous operation with ground control override

Results:

· Mission Duration: Extended from 2 to 15 years
· Power Density: Increased from 5 to 50 W/kg
· System Mass: Reduced by 60%
· Reliability: 99.99% over 15-year mission

